To use 

     GoogleCredentials credentials = GoogleCredentials.getApplicationDefault()

You must have the environment variable `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` must be defined pointing to a file defining the credentials. 

Other wise you can do it like shown in the [Google drive java quickstart](https://developers.google.com/drive/api/quickstart/java#step_2_set_up_the_sample)


    private static final String CREDENTIALS_FILE_PATH = &quot;/credentials.json&quot;;

    InputStream in = DriveQuickstart.class.getResourceAsStream(CREDENTIALS_FILE_PATH);
    if (in == null) {
      throw new FileNotFoundException(&quot;Resource not found: &quot; + CREDENTIALS_FILE_PATH);
    }
    GoogleClientSecrets clientSecrets =
        GoogleClientSecrets.load(JSON_FACTORY, new InputStreamReader(in));

